  <slide>
    <title>Keyboard Support: Sequential Navigation and Focus Visibility</title>
    <contents>
      <ol>
        <li>All functionality of a web page can be accomplished with the keyboard alone:
          <ul>
            <li>Sequentially moving through the links and form controls on a web page.</li>
            <li>Activating links, buttons and changing the states of checkboxes and radio buttons.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>The visual indication of focus must be easily identified:
          <ul>
            <li>A visible outline appears around the link or form control when it has focus.</li>
            <li>Keyboard focus must always be on visible element.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Bypass Blocks feature:
          <ul>
            <li><a href="https://paypal.github.io/skipto/">SkipTo Menu Button</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://webaim.org/techniques/skipnav/">"Skip To Main" link</a></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>Keyboard Support: Examples</title>
    <contents>
      <p><a href="https://accessibleit.disability.illinois.edu/course-web-a11y-concepts/examples/html/links-and-form-controls.html#default" target="_test">Test page for exploring the visual differences between passive and active focus styling.</a></p>
      <table class="table table-striped">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Web Page</th>
            <th>Sequential Navigation</th>
            <th>Focus Visible</th>
            <th>Bypass Blocks</th>
            <th>Notes</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><a href="https://fightingillini.com/" target="_test">Fighting Illini Home Page</a></td>
            <td>Incomplete</td>
            <td>Poor</td>
            <td>Link</td>
            <td>
              <ul>
                <li>Video controls are not keyboard accessible.</li>
                <li>Poor focus styling, relies on default focus styling with mixed results.</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><a href="https://zoom.us/" target="_test">Zoom Home Page</a></td>
            <td>Incomplete</td>
            <td>Poor</td>
            <td>Link</td>
            <td>
              <ul>
                <li>Keyboard activation for carousels operates on the second carousel and there is not sequential access to the carousel controls on the second carousel.</li>
                <li>Poor focus styling, inconsistent use of active and default focus styling creates missing or ambivelent focus indication.</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><a href="https://accessibleit.disability.illinois.edu/" target="_test">DRES Accessible IT Group</a></td>
            <td>Complete</td>
            <td>Good</td>
            <td>SkipTo Button</td>
            <td>
              <ul>
                <li>All links and controls can be accessed through the keyboard.</li>
                <li>Keyboard activation and pointer "click" on items have same results.</li>
                <li>Actively style keyboard focus to provide an outline around links and form controls.</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><a href="https://www.rutgers.edu/" target="_test">Rutgers University home page</a></td>
            <td>Complete</td>
            <td>Good</td>
            <td>Link</td>
            <td>
              <ul>
                <li>Sub-menu open/close controls not easy to discerne.</li>
                <li>If search opened, it is not automatically closed and obscures content.</li>
                <li>Generally good keyboard focus styling with use of a outline.</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><a href="https://webtheme.illinois.edu/" target="_test">Illinois Web Theme</a></td>
            <td>Complete</td>
            <td>Poor</td>
            <td>SkipTo Button</td>
            <td>
              <ul>
                <li>Some keyboard enhancements result in lost focus, using arrow keys when a menu is open.</li>
                <li>Poor keyboard focus, relies mostly on color changes and no outlining.</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>Keyboard Support: Testing</title>
    <contents>
      <ul>
        <li>Move your mouse away from your work station or cover your track pad to allow your attention to be only on using the keyboard.  <br/><em>Note: Recommend using Firefox since it's default focus styling is less apparent than Chrome or Safari.</em></li>
        <li>Use the <kbd>tab</kbd> key to navigate to links, form controls and other interactive content on the page.</li>
        <li>Questions:
          <ul>
            <li>Can I tell where keyboard focus is on the page?</li>
            <li>Using the <kbd>Tab</kbd> can I navigate to all the links and form controls on the page.</li>
            <li>Can I <em>activate</em> links, buttons, checkboxes and radio buttons using the <kbd>Space</kbd> or <kbd>Enter</kbd> keys?</li>
            <li>Does the navigation of links and form controls seem predictable?</li>
            <li>Does focus ever <em>disappear</em> and then magically reapear?</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </contents>
  </slide>

